cff-version: 1.2.0
message: |
  If you use hexa-bio in academic work, please cite as below. The cycle-25
  release (v1.1.0) covers numerical / formalism / infrastructure work only —
  no biological, clinical, regulatory, immunological, or therapeutic claim
  is made or implied. C3+ (wet-lab → IND → phase I) is explicitly
  out-of-repo per cross-cutting Require (R6).
title: "hexa-bio: 5-axis molecular-toolkit numerical primitive sandbox (HEXA family, biology axis)"
abstract: |
  hexa-bio is the empirical companion to the canon biology axis
  (https://github.com/dancinlab/canon). It implements a 5-axis
  numerical primitive sandbox (axis count locked): four bio "verbs" that
  form the n=6 invariant-lattice tetrahedron — composition (WEAVE),
  actuation (NANOBOT), catalysis (RIBOZYME), assembly (VIROCAPSID) — plus
  a fifth axis, computation (QUANTUM), an external qpu_bridge VQE compute
  layer over the qmirror substrate (H₂/LiH chemical/spectroscopic accuracy
  + ML pilots). A 16-cell in-silico matrix (4 bio axis × 4 disease class
  label) verifies the simulators against publicly catalogued disease-class
  marker metadata at IN-SILICO grade only. PASS criteria verify simulator +
  metadata internal consistency. They do NOT verify biological, structural,
  immunogenic, manufacturability, regulatory, or therapeutic-efficacy
  properties of any annotated marker.
