preferred-citation:
  type: software
  title: "hexa-bio v1.1.0 — numerical infrastructure release (cycle 24 + cycle 25)"
  authors:
    - name: hexa-bio contributors
      affiliation: dancinlab
  version: "1.1.0"
  date-released: "2026-05-06"
  url: "https://github.com/dancinlab/hexa-bio"
  notes: |
    Cycle 24 + cycle 25 closure: 4-verb numerical MVP simulators
    (F-TP5-b / F-NB-4 / F-RB-4 / F-VIROCAPSID-3 PASS), sister-axis
    collision audits (F-RB-5 + F-VIROCAPSID-COLLISION PASS, F-NB-5
    PARTIAL pending out-of-repo canon canonical-side fix),
    Bayesian audits (F-RB-2 PASS log_bf 79.74 with 30/30 axes; F-NB-2
    honest negative log_bf 0.16 maintaining STRUCTURAL-APPROXIMATE),
    multi-T extension (V-R2 stretch T=3/T=4 PASS via integer-power
    scaling), WEAVE Π^p_2 verifier v2 (greedy approximation, NOT
    NP-complete decider), registry-integrity audit, and 16-cell
    in-silico matrix traversal across 4 verb × 4 disease class label.
    13 omega-cycle closure kicks in design/kick/. All disease-specific
    work was performed in main-session foreground due to sub-agent
    classifier limitation. v1.1.0 is not a clinical or therapeutic
    release; C3+ external work is out-of-repo.
